parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission clutch can cause the vehicle to hesitate, jerk, or stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle vibrates or shudders when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift gears
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the check engine warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dual clutch can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the vehicle vibrates or shudders when shifting gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or makes unusual noises while driving; the check engine warning light is illuminated; the oil warning light is illuminated; the vehicle jerks or sputters while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to accelerate, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission shudders or hesitates while driving; the vehicle fails to accelerate; the transmission shifts into neutral while driving; the vehicle jerks or sputters while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position; the vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system problems can cause the vehicle to stall or lose motive power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates while driving; the check engine warning light is illuminated; the vehicle jerks or sputters while driving; the fuel pump fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil pump belt failure can cause the engine to seize or fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine makes unusual noises while driving; the oil warning light is illuminated; the vehicle stalls or loses power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the canister purge valve can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause fuel tank deformation and excessive vacuum in the fuel tank, which can lead to fuel pump problems and engine failure.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls

especially when refueling; the engine light comes on with code P1450; the vehicle shakes or shutters when starting; the fuel tank deforms; the fuel pump has problems; the engine has difficulty starting or stalls frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank deformation can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause fuel pump problems and engine failure.
symptoms: The fuel tank deforms; the vehicle stalls
especially when refueling; the engine light comes on with code P1450; the fuel pump has problems; the engine has difficulty starting or stalls frequently.
